    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A massive construct assembled from the bones of ancient Keepers, animated by Grafvitnir’s corrupted Root-Rune sorcery. Placed in the Emberwell to prevent any Keeper from completing the First Kindling rite. Twelve feet tall, built from hundreds of bones fused with black Rot-corruption. It guards the ember seed specifically. Its purpose is singular: prevent the ritual from completing.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Grave Smash</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): T1 4 dmg; T2 8 dmg + target pushed 5ft; T3 12 dmg + pushed 10ft + knocked prone.</li><li><strong>Rot Pulse</strong> (Main, Area 30ft, Reason, 2M): T1 3 necrotic; T2 5 necrotic + Intuition test or weakened EoNT; T3 7 necrotic + weakened EoNT all in range.</li><li><strong>Keeper’s Bane</strong> (Main, Ranged 30ft, Presence): Targets Kaelen only. T1 3 dmg; T2 6 dmg + Presence test or ritual interrupted (she must spend her action next turn to restart); T3 8 dmg + ritual interrupted + frightened EoNT.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Root-Bound:</strong> Cannot move more than 60ft from the ember seed. If forced beyond that range, teleports back adjacent to seed at end of its turn.</li><li><strong>Undying Purpose:</strong> Below 20 SP: +1 to attacks. Edge on Might defense tests vs. forced movement.</li><li><strong>Constructed Resilience:</strong> Immune to poison and disease effects.</li></ul><p><strong>MALICE</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Grafvitnir’s Decree (3M):</strong> Single target 40ft, Presence test: failure = 3d6 necrotic + frightened (save ends).</li></ul><p><strong>BEAT 19 TACTICS:</strong> Targets Kaelen above all others. Stays adjacent to ember seed. Will use Keeper’s Bane every turn it has an action. Grave Smash on anyone who gets adjacent. Rot Pulse when 3+ heroes cluster.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
